It is hard to put my love for peppino’s into words. My husband and I are regulars and we love it so much that we hosted the out-of-towners dinner for our wedding there (pre-pandemic!). Their pizza is classic Brooklyn style, as good as (or better than!) Juliana’s or anywhere else. But what’s truly great about peppino’s is that they offer so many other good dishes beyond pizza: their heroes are served on their fresh bread from their brick oven, their meatballs are perfect, the eggplant parm is textbook, the Caesar salad is best in its category... and you have to get some garlic crisps to go with everything. Carmela and the rest of the staff are so friendly and will go above and beyond to make you feel at home (when dining in is safe again). Cannot recommend highly enough.

Peppino’s is one of those special neighborhood places that can feel like a second home. From the classic red-and-white tablecloths to the pizza oven in back, the waitstaff and the music—the place is authentic and the food is always delicious. Favorites include the eggplant parm sandwich, diavola pizza, garlic bread; the list goes on. It’s worth noting that Peppino’s has a unique pizza crust, which they also use for their sandwiches: crisp but hearty; not too thin, while neither doughy not tough. One of the top crusts in NYC for sure. And most importantly, Peppino’s is consistent—the food hasn’t disappointed even once in my 6 years of in-person and delivery orders. Only complaint is that you pay a little extra for the quality—but when you want quality eats, this place is worth it.

It is located in Park Slope, which is one of the very nice areas of Brooklyn. This place is known for the great brick oven pizza with garlic crisps, according to my friends. So, I visited there with one of my friends recently.  The freshly brick oven baked pizza (Margherita pizza) there was sublime. It was one of the best pizzas, which I had in Brooklyn and Manhattan. And it was significantly cheaper than their competitors in Manhattan or even Brooklyn. The quality of pizza in Brooklyn is generally high but this restaurant had significantly good one, in my personal opinion.  The staff there were all very friendly, helpful, and social.  The garlic crisps were also amazingly good with full of garlicky flavors. (I personally love stronger garlic flavor, so, it was perfect to my liking.)  They had Manhattan quality with Brooklyn price.  I highly recommend this place. *****

Good pizza shop (formerly Aiello's) that is family-run and accommodating to all diners, whether you're taking advantage of table service or grabbing a slice or two. They accept credit cards (nice if you're short on cash, even for a few slices). The pizza itself is a perfect Brooklyn slice, with the right amount of cheese, sauce and crust.

The restaurant is designed nicely and the customer service rocks.  The owners of this restaurant had a pizzeria in this exact location for over 25 years; an old fashion but good NY slice place. They closed for a few months, and then opened up this great new dining experience. Now you can get reasonably priced excellent brick oven pizza in the heart of Park Slope, imported beers and even some dessert options.
